      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUPER STITCH (2) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (17.79) at Mt Gambier over 305m. Key chance in this line up. MOLLY ROCHELLE (6) has an honest record despite remaining a maiden and is long overdue for a win, having placed seven of 12 career runs. Will give a great sight again. INGA JOKER (4) has shown decent speed at his last couple and filled minor placings, last time finishing third beaten 6 lengths (22.84). Yet to win here but has run some good races including two placings. Winning chance. PAW GEORGIE (7) can fill a top-three spot.",
